UID:15600
DTSTAMP:20260311T170241Z
SUMMARY:LitLounge
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/litlounge-15600
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20251201T174034Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20251229T192140Z
DESCRIPTION:This month we will be discussing Half Life by Jillian Cantor.In
  this thought provoking and lyrical novel\, the author reimagines the life
  of Nobel-Prize-winning scientist Marie Curie in two parallel timelines. O
 ne timeline reflects her real-world achievements and the other explores ho
 w the world might be different had she made other choices.Presented in par
 tnership with Morton Grove Public Library.Find Half Life in the library ca
 talog.Keyword: Book Lovers
CATEGORIES:Books and Authors,Discussion
