LAST-MODIFIED:20260218T222917Z
DESCRIPTION:Standing Above the Clouds From filmmaker Jalena Keane-Lee\, t
 his documentary shows the grassroots movement led by women from three Nati
 ve Hawaiian families to stop a massive telescope from being built on the s
 acred mountain\, Mauna Kea. It explores themes of intergenerational heali
 ng\, cultural preservation\, community activism\, environmental impact\, a
 nd the emotional toll on those involved. After watching the film together
 \, join Chris and Sharon in a discussion with filmmaker Jalena Keane-Lee.2
 024 : 83 minutes : Not rated : DocumentaryFree tickets will be given to th
 ose who attend.Watch the trailer for Standing Above the Clouds.Find Standi
 ng Above the Clouds in the library catalog.
