UID:1842
DTSTAMP:20260311T170242Z
SUMMARY:Young Steinway Concert
URL;VALUE=URI:https://www.skokielibrary.info/event/young-steinway-concert-1
 842
STATUS:CONFIRMED
CREATED:20250730T195806Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260304T172955Z
DESCRIPTION:Alison Chung\, a senior at Glenbrook North High School\, studie
 s violin with Desirée Ruhstrat. Alison was recently named runner-up in th
 e ADM Concerto Competition and performed the first movement of the Walton 
 Violin Concerto with the Kishwaukee Symphony Orchestra. As a member of Qua
 rtetto Speranza\, she received the Bronze Medal in the Junior Division at 
 the 2025 Fischoff National Chamber Music Competition. With the Phoenix Qua
 rtet\, she earned second prize at the 2026 Rembrandt Chamber Music Competi
 tion and first prize in the Open Division of the Chicago National Chamber 
 Music Competition.Duo Dunamis consists of pianists David Goetz and Ryan Hu
 . David is a junior at Loyola Academy and Ryan is a junior at North Shore 
 Country Day School. Both have been awarded first place for both duo and so
 lo performance in the American Protege Music Competition and performed at 
 Weill Recital Hall at Carnegie Hall. The duo has appeared in the Chicago D
 uo Piano Music Festival\, the Plymouth Concert Series\, and the Merion Con
 cert Series.Pianist Pratyay Rao is a junior at New Trier Township High Sch
 ool. He studies piano with Lyudmila Lakisova. Pratyay won second place in 
 the 2025 American Fine Arts Festival International Concerto Competition\, 
 was a finalist in 2024 New Trier Concerto Competition\, and won first plac
 e in the 2024 Charleston Summer Music Competition. Pratyay also participat
 es in Science Olympiad and DECA competitions.Free tickets will be given to
  those present starting at 2:30 pm.
CATEGORIES:Arts and Culture
DTSTART:20260503T200000Z
DTEND:20260503T211500Z
LOCATION:5215 Oakton Street\, Skokie\, IL\, 60077\, US
ROOM:Petty Auditorium
